Supplier - name - Inform the relevant field with the full name of the supplier. If the supplier is a computer or payroll service provider supplying the data on behalf of the payer, the name of the service provider must inform the field.

Multi-word surnames must be separated by a single space. If the payee has no surname this field must be blank filled. Payees with a single name only may provide their name information in either the given name field or the surname field.

Supplier - Australian business number - Inform the relevant field with the valid Australian Business Number (ABN). The ABN must belong to the entity named in this form.
Payer - Australian business number - Inform the relevant field with the valid Australian Business Number (ABN). The ABN must belong to the entity named in this form.

Payee Tax file number

Payee - tax file number - Inform the relevant field with the Tax File Number (TFN) of the payee. In circumstances where a payee is not required to quote or has chosen not to quote a TFN, one of the appropriate TFN Exemption Codes must be used in place of the TFN. The code '000000000' should inform the field where the payee chooses not to quote a TFN or fails to provide one within the 14 day reporting period. The code '987654321' should inform the field where payee has quoted a TFN with non-numeric characters. This code must also be used where the TFN quoted cannot be contained in the TFN field.
Payee Tax File Number Exemption Code

Payee - TFN Exemption Code - Inform the relevant field with the appropriate code to indicate the reason a Tax File Number (TFN) is not being quoted by the payee. A payee may choose to be exempt from quoting a Tax File Number (TFN) at the time of Declaration, which is indicated by a TFN Exemption Code. The codes are 1 for Payee applying for a TFN, 3 for Payee under eighteen, and 4 for Payee is a pensioner.

Payee Individual Non Business Gross payments

Payee - DINB - Individual Non Business Gross payments - Inform the relevant field with the total gross amount before amounts are withheld for tax. Inform the field with the gross payments in whole dollars. Do not include cent values in this field.
Payee Total allowances

Payee - DINB - Total allowances - Inform the relevant field with the total allowances are amounts paid by employers to cover anticipated costs or as compensation for conditions of employment. Allowances may include car, travel or transport allowances, award transport payments covering either transport or car expenses which are paid under an industrial law or award that was in force on 29 October 1986, allowances for tools, clothing or laundry, dirt, height, site, risk, meal or entertainment allowances, allowances for qualifications for example, a first aid certificate, or any reimbursement of car expenses that are calculated by reference to the distance travelled by the car which is an exempt car expense payment benefit for fringe benefits tax purposes. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cent values in this field.
Payee Lump sum payment A

Payee - DINB - Lump sum payment A - Inform the relevant field with the amount at lump sum A representing the amount paid for unused long service leave that accrued after 15 August 1978 but before 18 August 1993; unused holiday pay and other leave related payments that accrued before 18 August 1993, or unused long service leave accrued after 17 August 1993 or unused holiday pay or related payments, where the amount was paid in connection with a payment that includes, or consists of a genuine redundancy payment, an early retirement scheme payment or the invalidity segment of an employment termination payment or superannuation payment. Inform the field with only dollar values. Do not include cents values.
Payee Lump sum payment B

Payee - DINB - Lump sum payment B - Inform the releavnt field with the amount at lump sum B representing the amount paid for unused long service leave that accrued before 16 August 1978. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Lump sum payment D

Payee - DINB - Lump sum payment D - Inform the relevant field with the amount at lump sum D representing the amount of genuine redundancy payment or early retirement scheme payment below the tax-free threshold. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Lump sum payment E

Payee - DINB - Lump sum payment E - Inform the releavnt field with the amount at lump sum E representing the amount for back payment of certain amounts including a payment of salary or wages that accrued more than 12 months ago. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Community development employment project

Payee - DINB - Community development employment project - Inform the relevant field with the Community Development Employment Project (CDEP) payment. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Exempt foreign employment income

Payee - DINB - Exempt foreign employment income - Inform the relevant field with any amounts paid to the payee that are exempt foreign employment income. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Reportable fringe benefits

Payee - DINB - Reportable fringe benefits - Inform the relevant field with the reportable fringe benefits are where the total taxable value of the fringe benefits provided to a payee by a payer supplying a payment summary in the FBT year (1 April to 31 March) exceeds the limit. The grossed-up taxable value of those benefits must be recorded on the payee's payment summary as the reportable fringe benefits amount. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DINB - Individual Non Business Total tax withheld - Inform the relevant field with the amount of tax withheld from the payee's individual non-business income. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cent values in this field.

Payee - DLVP - Total tax withheld - Inform the relevant field with the total amounts of tax paid by the entity (payer) to the Commissioner for personal services income attributed to an individual. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DEMP - ETP total tax withheld - Inform the relevant field with the amount of tax withheld from the payee's income from an Employment Termination Payment (ETP). Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DSLS - Superannuation Lump Sum Total tax withheld - Inform the relevant field with the amount of tax withheld from the payee's income from an Superannuation Lump Sum payment. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DPEN - Superannuation Income Stream Tax withheld - Inform the relevant field with the amount of tax withheld from payments made as a result of a superannuation Income stream for the financial year. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee ETP Tax free component
Payee Lump sum in arrears - tax free component
Payee Superannuation Income Stream Tax Free component
Payee Superannuation Lump Sum Tax Free component

Payee - DEMP - ETP Tax free component - Inform the relevant field with theamount of the payment which is non-assessable and non-exempt income. For employment termination payments, the tax free component consists of any pre July 1983 segment plus any invalidity segment of the payment. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DPEN - Lump sum in arrears - tax free component - Inform the relevant field with the tax free component of payments received as a lump sum (or single payment) for a superannuation income stream amount that accrued in previous year or years. Inform the field with the dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DPEN - Superannuation Income Stream Tax Free component - Inform the relevant field with the Superannuation Income Stream Tax Free component. For new superannuation income streams from 1 July 2007, the tax free component is made up of the contributions segment and crystallised segment. The contributions segment consists of contributions made to a fund on or after 1 July 2007 which have not been, and will not be, included in the assessable income of the fund. The crystallised segment may consist of any of the following amounts as at just before 1 July 2007: - The pre-July 1983 component- The concessional component - Undeducted contributions - Post-June 1994 invalidity component - CGT exempt component. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DSLS - Superannuation Lump Sum Tax Free component - Inform the relevant field with the Superannuation Lump Sum Tax Free component. For superannuation lump sum from 1 July 2007, the tax free component is made up of the contributions segment and crystallised segment. The contributions segment consists of contributions made to a fund on or after 1 July 2007 which have not been, and will not be, included in the assessable income of the fund. The crystallised segment may consist of any of the following amounts as at just before 1 July 2007. These are the pre-July 1983 component, the concessional component, undeducted contributions, post-June 1994 invalidity component and the CGT exempt component. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Superannuation Income Stream Taxable component - taxed element
Payee Lump sum in arrears - taxable component - taxed element
Payee Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component - taxed element

Payee - DPEN - Superannuation Income Stream Taxable component - taxed element - Inform the relevant field with the taxed element that is the amount of the taxable component of the superannuation income stream that represents the return of amounts that have been subject to tax in the fund. The Superannuation Income Stream Taxable component is obtained by subtracting the Tax Free component from the Superannuation Income Stream total amount. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DPEN - Lump sum in arrears - taxable component - taxed element - Inform the relevant field with the taxable component of payments received as a lump sum (or single payment) for a superannuation income stream amount that accrued in a previous year or years. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DSLS - Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component - taxed element - Inform the relevant field with the Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component of the superannuation lump sum that represents the return of amounts that have been subject to tax in the fund. The Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component is obtained by subtracting the Tax Free component from the Superannuation Lump Sum total amount. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Superannuation Income Stream Taxable component - untaxed element
Payee Lump sum in arrears - taxable component - untaxed element
Payee Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component - untaxed element

Payee - DPEN - Superannuation Income Stream Taxable component - untaxed element - Inform the relevant field with the untaxed element that represents the return of amounts (other than the tax free component) that have been subject to tax in the fund. This usually occurs because the superannuation income stream is sourced at least in part from a scheme that is not subject to tax. The Superannuation Income Stream Taxable component is obtained by subtracting the Tax Free component from the Superannuation Income Stream total amount. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values. Do not include cents

Payee - DPEN - Lump sum in arrears - taxable component - untaxed element - Inform the relevant field with the taxable component of payments received as a lump sum (or single payment) for a superannuation income stream amount that accrued in a previous year or years. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.

Payee - DSLS - Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component - untaxed element - Inform the relevant field with the Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component untaxed element that represents amounts (other than the tax free component) that have not been subject to tax in a fund. The Superannuation Lump Sum Taxable component is obtained by subtracting the Tax Free component from the Superannuation Lump Sum total amount. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee ETP Taxable component

Payee - DEMP - ETP Taxable component - Inform the relevant field with the total amount of the employment termination payment less the tax free component of the payment. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee ETP Transitional termination payment

Payee - DEMP - Transitional termination payment - Inform the relevant field with the amount of the termination payment made before 1 July 2012 in accordance with transitional arrangements which apply where a person is entitled, as at 9 May 2006, to a payment on termination of employment under a written contract, Australian or foreign law, legal instrument made under such a law or workplace agreement made under the Workplace Relations Act 1996. Inform the field with dollar values only. Do not include cents values.
Payee Current payment related to a prior payment for the same termination

Payee - DEMP - Current payment related to a prior payment for the same termination - Inform the relevant field with the appropriate code to determine whether a prior payment for the same termination has occurred. The codes are Y for Yes or N for No. An employment termination payment paid in a year of income where another employment termination payment has already been paid earlier in consequence of the same termination of employment. This is whether the earlier payment was made in the same income year, or a *earlier year of income (*except for the 2007/2008 year). Note. In 2007/2008 there is no requirement to indicate this if the only prior payment was made in an earlier year.This field must be informed of one of the enumerated values.
Payee Reportable employer superannuation contributions

Payee - DINB - Reportable employer superannuation contributions - Inform the relevant field with the amount of reportable employer superannuation contributions. Reportable employer superannuation contributions are the portion of the employer contribution that the employee has influenced, i.e. superannuation contributions made by the employer under the terms of a salary sacrifice agreement. Reportable employer superannuation contributions do not include: super guarantee contributions, contributions mandated by industrial agreements that the employee does not influence, or post tax member contributions.

Payee - DLVP - Reportable employer superannuation contributions - Inform the relevant field with the amount of reportable employer superannuation contributions. Reportable employer superannuation contributions are the portion of the employer contribution that the employee has influenced, i.e. superannuation contributions made by the employer under the terms of a salary sacrifice agreement. Reportable employer superannuation contributions do not include: super guarantee contributions, contributions mandated by industrial agreements that the employee does not influence, or post tax member contributions.

Payee Superannuation Lump Sum Date of Payment
Payee - DEMP - Date of payment - Inform the relevant field with the date (day, month, year) on which the payment for goods or services was made.

Payee Business and Personal Services Payment type

Payee - DINB - Income type - Inform the relevant field with the appropriate code for one of the enumerated values. The codes for the field are S for Salary and Wages or P for Non-Superannuation pension or annuity payments.

Payee - DLVP - Payment type - Inform the relevant field with the appropriate code to identify the type of income being reported on the payment summary. The codes are 001 for Labour Hire or 002 for Other Specified. This field must be informed with one of the enumerated values.
Payee Labour Hire Gross Payment
Payee - DLVP - Labour Hire Gross Payment - This is the amount of income earned by the payee, including the market value of non-cash benefits. Do not include cents.
Payee Other Payment Specified by Regulation
Payee - DLVP - Other Payment Specified by Regulation - This is the amount of income earned by the payee, including the market value of non-cash benefits. Do not include cents.
Payee Lump Sum payment A Type

Payee - DINB - Lump Sum payment A Type - Inform the relevant field with the allowed indicator for the Lump sum payment A type. If the field is greater than zero, this field must be set to one of the allowable indicators as specified below: R = where payment was for a genuine redundancy, invalidity or under an early retirement scheme. T = where payment was not a payment for a genuine redundancy, invalidity or under an early retirement scheme. Blank fill this field if Lump sum payment A field is zero.
Payee Workplace giving

Payee - DINB - Workplace giving - Employers and their staff can choose to donate to any organisation they like as long as the organisation is eligible to receive tax deductible gifts, that is, the organisation must be a deductible gift recipient (DGR).
Payee Union/professional association fees
Payee - DINB - Union/professional association fees - Inform the relevant field with the total of amounts paid to unions or professional bodies on behalf of the employee.
